This paper discusses a model of content and access provider revenues in information-centric networks, which falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also mentions concave demand and utility functions, which are commonly used in information theory (cs.IT) and game theory (cs.GT). The paper also discusses the effect of caching on the revenue model, which is related to security and privacy (cs.CR) and distributed computing (cs.DC). Finally, the paper mentions a demand-response model, which is related to social and information networks (cs.SI).
